cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.SD 

The paper deals with natural language processing and binary classification, which are both subfields of computer science. The use of probabilistic models and machine learning techniques suggests that the paper could belong to the categories of computational linguistics (cs.CL), machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), information retrieval (cs.IR), or sound and music computing (cs.SD). However, since the focus is on language processing and classification, cs.CL is the most likely category, followed by cs.LG and cs.AI.
